Sentencas: Protonic solid oxide fuel cells (P - SOFCs) is an active field in development of intermediate -temperature fuel cells to render high power density and durability.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate

Sentencas: The use of pulsed laser deposition (PLD) to deposit the functional layers and interlayers of P - SOFCs supported on anode substrates offers advantages in reducing both the ohmic and polarization resistances of the cell, which however critically depends on the substrate microstructure.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate

Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate

Sentencas: 3- delta (BCZYYb) powders to prepare anode substrates with large, interconnected cylindrical pores, followed by using electrophoretic deposition to deposit NiO-BCZYYb as pore filler to fill the pores exposed on the top surface.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate

Sentencas: With an anode substrate made using 20 wt% paper fiber and PLD-deposited NiO-BCZYYb anode functional layer (AFL), NiO-BCZYYb anode interlayer, and BCZYYb electrolyte layer, the peak power density reaches 550 mW/cm 2 at 600 degrees C, which is 30 % higher than that of the cell with a commercial half -cell composed of NiO-BCZYYb substrate and spin -coated BCZYYb electrolyte layer but the same cathode interlayer and cathode layer.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate

Sentencas: Furthermore, the insertion of a PLD-deposited graded anode interlayer between the AFL and electrolyte layer is found to be critical for high cell durability.
Titulo: Intermediate-temperature protonic solid oxide fuel cell made of pulsed laser deposition-based functional layers and interlayers on an optimally tailored anode substrate
